  "text": "The scheduler binding decision reaches the kubelet through a multi-step process involving the scheduler, API server, and kubelet components:\n\n## 1. Scheduler Binding Phase\n\nIn **pkg/scheduler/schedule_one.go**, the `Scheduler.bind()` method (line 968) orchestrates the binding process. It first calls `Scheduler.extendersBinding()` (line 982) to check if any extender plugins want to handle binding, then falls back to framework plugins via `fwk.RunBindPlugins()` (line 978).\n\nThe framework's `RunBindPlugins()` in **pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/framework.go** (line 1286) iterates through registered bind plugins until one succeeds.\n\n## 2. Default Binder Plugin\n\nThe default bind plugin is implemented in **pkg/scheduler/framework/plugins/defaultbinder/default_binder.go**. The `DefaultBinder.Bind()` method (line 51) creates a Binding object and calls `b.handle.ClientSet().CoreV1().Pods(binding.Namespace).Bind()` (line 58) to make an API server request.\n\n## 3. API Server Binding Handler\n\nThe API server receives the binding request in **pkg/registry/core/pod/storage/storage.go**. The `BindingREST.Create()` method (line 173) validates the binding and calls `assignPod()` (line 194), which calls `setPodHostAndAnnotations()` (line 209). This method uses `store.Storage.GuaranteedUpdate()` (line 226) to atomically update the pod's `spec.nodeName` field in etcd while preventing concurrent modifications via preconditions.\n\n## 4. Kubelet Pod Watch Setup\n\nThe kubelet watches for pod updates from the API server through **pkg/kubelet/config/apiserver.go**. The `NewSourceApiserver()` function (line 37) creates a ListWatcher that filters pods with `spec.nodeName == this_node` using a field selector. The `newSourceApiserverFromLW()` function (line 58) uses a Reflector to watch for changes and sends PodUpdate events through the updates channel.\n\n## 5. Kubelet Sync Loop\n\nThe **pkg/kubelet/kubelet.go** contains the main synchronization loop:\n\n- `Kubelet.syncLoop()` (line 2387) receives pod updates from the config source channel\n- `Kubelet.syncLoopIteration()` (line 2461) dispatches updates to appropriate handlers based on operation type (ADD, UPDATE, REMOVE, etc.)\n- For new pods, `Kubelet.HandlePodAdditions()` (line 2601) is called\n\n## 6. Pod Admission Gates\n\nIn `HandlePodAdditions()` (line 2637-2676), the kubelet calls `Kubelet.canAdmitPod()` (line 2650 and 2666). This method (defined at line 2349) iterates through registered admission handlers from `kl.admitHandlers` (line 2355-2357).\n\nAdmission handlers are implemented in **pkg/kubelet/lifecycle/interfaces.go** and related files:\n\n- **interfaces.go** (line 41-44) defines the `PodAdmitHandler` interface with the `Admit()` method\n- **handlers.go** (line 207-232) implements `NewAppArmorAdmitHandler()` for AppArmor validation\n- **predicate.go** implements `NewPredicateAdmitHandler()` (line 100) which checks node resources, OS compatibility, and other constraints\n\nAdditional admission handlers registered in kubelet.go include:\n- Eviction manager (line 947)\n- Sysctls allowlist (line 956)\n- Container manager resources (line 966)\n- Predicate admission handler (line 969)\n- AppArmor handler (line 978)\n- Node shutdown manager (line 1014)\n\n## 7. Pod Worker and SyncPod\n\nIf the pod passes admission, `Kubelet.HandlePodAdditions()` calls `podWorkers.UpdatePod()` (line 2677) in **pkg/kubelet/pod_workers.go** (line 735). This schedules the pod for synchronization.\n\nEventually, `Kubelet.SyncPod()` (line 1845) is called, which:\n- Generates API pod status (line 1899)\n- Sets pod status (line 1926)\n- Ensures referenced secrets/configmaps are registered (lines 1936-1939)\n- Handles resource resizing (line 1892)\n- Proceeds with pod setup and container creation\n\n## Summary\n\nThe binding decision flows as:\nScheduler.bind() → DefaultBinder.Bind() → API Server (BindingREST.Create) → etcd (updates spec.nodeName) → Kubelet watches via ListWatcher → syncLoopIteration() → HandlePodAdditions() → Admission Gates (canAdmitPod) → podWorkers.UpdatePod() → SyncPod()"
